ğŸ”¹What is React JS?
React JS (or simply React) is an open-source JavaScript library developed by Facebook for building user interfaces, especially single-page applications (SPAs).
It helps developers build fast, dynamic, and interactive web applications by creating reusable UI components.

ğŸ”¹Key Features of React JS:
Feature	                Description
ğŸ” Component-Based	   Build UIs using small, reusable components.
âš¡ Virtual DOM	       Improves performance by updating only what's necessary in the DOM.
ğŸ§  Declarative	       Describe what the UI should look like, and React takes care of the rendering.
ğŸ§± JSX	               JavaScript + HTML syntax for writing UI code.
ğŸ“¦ Unidirectional DataFlow	: Data flows in one direction â€” from parent to child (via props).
ğŸ”§ Hooks	             Functions like useState and useEffect for managing state and side effects in functional components.


